%I A394782 #24 Apr 18 2026 17:09:01
%S A394782 3,7,31,211,2311,15017,102107,1616621,22309297,3234846617,
%T A394782 200560490131,3710369067407,27659114866121,1868965904524297,
%U A394782 307444891294245707,794857523833903571,961380175077106319537,23457676271881394196659,1571664310216053411175823
%N A394782 a(n) is the largest prime of the form prime(n)#/d + d where p# denotes the product of all primes <= p and d divides prime(n)#.
%C A394782 d is a squarefree number (A005117).
%C A394782 Prime of the form prime(n)#/d+d with d = A295741(n).
%C A394782 Conjecture: sequence is increasing (i.e., a(n+1) > a(n) for any n >= 1).
%C A394782 Similar conjecture: A295741(n) < prime(n).
%e A394782 For n=6, 2*3*5*7*11*13/2 + 2 = 30030/2 + 2 = 15017 is prime, while 30031 is not prime, so a(6) = 15017.
%o A394782 (PARI) a(n) = my(Primo=vecprod(primes(n))); for(D=1, Primo, if(Primo%D==0 && ispseudoprime(Primo/D+D), return(Primo/D+D)));
%Y A394782 Cf. A002110, A005117, A365021, A182987.
%Y A394782 Cf. A006862, A014545, A295741.
%K A394782 nonn,new
%O A394782 1,1
